Package de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.exception

Contains the custom exceptions used throughout the eyetracking library.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ETErrorHandler
    Translates status codes returned by the IView X SDK functions to exceptions.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ETAoiException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a Area of Interest (AOI) related error occurred.
    ETBufferException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a buffer related error occurred.
    ETCalibrationException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a calibration related error occurred.
    ETConnectionException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a connection related error occurred.
    ETDeviceException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a device specific error occurred.
    ETException
    An exception that provides information on an eyetracker or eyetracking server related error.
    ETFileFormatException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a file-formatting related error occurred.
    ETParameterException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a parameter related error occurred.
    ETRecordingException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a recording related exception occurred.
    ETServerException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a server related error occurred.
    ETSocketException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a socket related error occurred.
    ETStreamException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a stream related error occurred.
    ETValidationException
    The subclass of ETException that is thrown when a validation related error occurred.

Package de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.exception Description

Contains the custom exceptions used throughout the eyetracking library. All exceptions inherit the base runtime exception class ETException.
